	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Repro steps:&#xD;&#xA;First use Debug Book: Go to region &gt; Act 1 &gt; UND - Underdark &gt; Fearful Rothe&#xD;&#xA;Several variations in dialogue depending on what player does from here:&#xD;&#xA;Variation 1: Use roll amazing. Walk towards the nearby Rothe to trigger a conversation with Skarjall.  Pick 1 &gt; 2. Then talk to the Rothe. Pick 2 and roll the dice.&#xD;&#xA;Variation 2: Use roll amazing. Walk towards the nearby Rothe to trigger a conversation with Skarjall.  Pick 1 &gt; 1 &gt; 1, roll dice, then Pick 1. Next talk to the Rothe. Pick 2 and roll dice.&#xD;&#xA;Variation 3: Walk towards the nearby Rothe to trigger a conversation with Skarjall.  Pick Leave. Then Ctrl+Shift+K on the Cave-In (the rubble behind the Rothe)." />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="64" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="Duergar dialog that happens if the player attacks / destroys the wall  by fearful rothe." />
			<children>
